/* ex2.5
** Determine the type of each of the following literals. Explain
the differences among the literals in each of the four examples:
*/

(a) 'a' - character literal, type is char
    L'a' - wide character literal, type is wchar_t
    "a" - string literal, type is string
    L"a" - wide string literal, type is string
(b) 10 - decimal integer literal, type is int
    10u - unsigned decimal integer literal, type is unsigned int
    10L - long decimal literal, type is long
    10uL - unsigned decimal literal, type is unsigned long
    012 - octal literal, type is int
    0xC - hexadecimal literal, type is int
(c) 3.14 - floating-point literal, type is double
    3.14f - single-precision floating-point literal, type is float
    3.14L - extended-precision floating-point literal, type is long double
(d) 10 - decimal integer literal, type is int
    10u - unsigned decimal integer literal, type is unsigned int
    10. - double-precision floating-point literal, type is double
    10e-2 - exponent floating-point literal, type is double
